se.hig.exte.repository

Interface CourseRepository

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<Course,java.lang.Integer>, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<Course,java.lang.Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<Course,java.lang.Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.query.QueryByExampleExecutor<Course>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<Course,java.lang.Integer>

    @Repository
public interface CourseRepository
extends org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<Course,java.lang.Integer>
    An interface used for database operations on Course objects. References to this interface are automatically given an implementation by Spring Boot when using the Autowired annotation.

        Parameters:
        name - The name String that the fetched Course objects should contain.
        courseCode - The course code String that the fetched Course objects should contain.
